## The examples you asked about

```js
cron.schedule('1 * * * * *')
```

➡ Runs every minute at second 1:

```text
10:00:01
10:01:01
10:02:01
```

---

```js
cron.schedule('10 * * * * *')
```

➡ Runs every minute at second 10:

```text
10:00:10
10:01:10
10:02:10
```

---

```js
cron.schedule('0 * * * * *')
```

➡ Runs every minute at second 0:

```text
10:00:00
10:01:00
10:02:00
```

---

```js
cron.schedule('0 */1 * * * *')
```

➡ Same as above (every minute):

```text
10:00:00
10:01:00
10:02:00
```

---

### One-line rule to remember

**Read cron left to right as:**

```text
Second Minute Hour Day Month Weekday
```

and ask:

> "At what second? At what minute? At what hour?"

When the current clock time matches all those values, the job runs.
